    "All scores were within the typical range (SLRT: all P R words ≥ 31, P R pseudowords ≥ 16, higher than or equal to the cut-off value of 16 [53]; RST-ARR: all P R ≥ 61, higher than the cut-off value of 16; RAN: maximum of 1 error and RT < 22.3 seconds in the categories letters and numbers; AQ: all participants AQ ≤ 20, under the cut-off value of 32).",
    "Experimental paradigm Main experimentA trial consisted of a sequence of up to eight repetitions of a pure tone separated by a constant interstimulus-interval ISI = 500 ms (Figure 1).",
    "Trials contained one omission (a missing pure tone) with probability p 0 = 6/7.",
    "Omissions occurred at position 4, 5, or 6 in the sequence.",
    "We asked the participants to attend and report, via a button press, the position of the omission within the sequence, if any."
